  {
    "uid": "doi:10.2139/ssrn.6531438",
    "drop": false,
    "field": "management",
    "role": "object",
    "bullets": [
      "A conceptual paper with no empirical sample, reassessing the enterprise-software make-or-buy decision by combining transaction cost economics and the resource-based view with an assessment of current AI capabilities.",
      "No language model is used by the authors; the paper analyzes how agentic generative-AI coding systems reshape seven make-or-buy determinants, names no specific model, and reports no validation.",
      "It argues the SaaSocalypse thesis is overstated: Make is most compelling for commodity utilities and differentiating custom applications, while regulated and mission-critical systems remain in the buy domain."
    ],
